## Completion 2026-06-18

Built end-to-end this session:
- `c:/code_files/spaarke-prototype/feature/uat-harness-framework` branch (commit `73a9ddc`) — pushed to origin
- 25 files added: `_infra/` (mocks + seed + vite alias), `_templates/prod-component-harness/` (copy-able scaffold), `projects/smart-todo-r4-uat/` (first consumer), `projects/_framework-setup-2026-06/README.md` (design doc), `claude.md` update (AI convention)
- Build verified: 2,181 modules transformed, 579 KB bundle in 7.75s
- Framework reusable: any future project copies `_templates/prod-component-harness/` + sets `SPAARKE_REPO_ROOT` env var to point at its worktree

### Future-state workflow (the iteration loop this enables)

```
1. Project starts (design-to-spec / project-pipeline) — unchanged
2. NEW: First task copies _templates/prod-component-harness/ → projects/<project>-uat/
3. task-execute writes code in production worktree
   ◆ Harness HMR-reloads on every save (sub-second)
4. Pre-deploy review: walk through harness; catch chrome/UX issues
5. master-deploy only when ready for integration UAT
6. Integration UAT: Xrm-real behaviors only (drag-persist, BroadcastChannel, auth)
7. merge-to-master — unchanged
```

Estimated saving for visual-heavy projects: ~30 min per UAT cycle compressed to sub-second; eliminates entire "post-deploy chrome rework wave" pattern that drove smart-todo-r4 Wave D + Wave E.

### Boundaries (what the harness does NOT replace)

- Master-deploy is still required for Xrm-real behaviors
- Integration UAT is still required
- Automated UI tests (R4-093 pattern) still run against deployed bits

### Reference

- Framework PR: TBD (will open from `feature/uat-harness-framework` to `main` in spaarke-prototype when ready to land)
